ite dwarf (WD)\nenshrouded by 0.6-0.7 solar masses of C/O-rich material, as it could result\nfrom a merger of two massive C/O WDs. This model reproduces the late light\ncurve of SN 2009dc well. A flux deficit at peak may be compensated by light\nfrom the interaction of the ejecta with the surrounding material.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Apr 2013 20:08:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 3 May 2013 18:29:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
