esis model, varying the\nopacity law and the strength of migration, as well as investigating the effect\nof disc truncation during the fragmentation process. Our early results suggest\nthat GI plus tidal downsizing is not the principal mode of planet formation,\nbut remains an excellent means of forming gas giant planets, brown dwarfs and\nlow mass stars at large semimajor axes. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Apr 2013 21:40:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
