 the WR star\nwinds, and does not rule out WR stars as the HeII ionization source. We study\nsystematic aperture effects on the detection and measurement of the WR\nfeatures, using SDSS spectra combined with the power of IFS. In this regard,\nthe importance of targeting low metallicity nearby systems is discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Apr 2013 14:57:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
